24/07/2003
BUCHAREST, Romania -- On Saturday (26 July), Foreign Minister Mircea Geoana will leave for a week-long visit to the United States.
Aides say Geoana will meet with several senior officials, including US Secretary of State Colin Powell.
In other news, the foreign ministry said Wednesday that Romania would close its missions to Sudan and Yemen as part of an ongoing process to reorganise diplomatic activities.
According to the ministry, maintenance costs for the embassies far exceed the amount of trade between Romania and the two countries.
(Rompres - 24/07/03;
Rompres - 23/07/03)
